entries.femaleVariant: Must be hard for you alone.
You and River are OK now?
Can't be easy raisin' three kids on your own.
Well it wasn't any easier with my husband.
In fact, the best days were when he didn't come home.
There were times I wished he'd disappear for a month just to not have him hang around.
Everything OK between you and River?
Yeah, finally found common ground. Better late than never.
Silver lining, considering the circumstances...
Hope it's nothin' but bright days ahead for Randy.
You never know with him, I swear. Not since he lost his father.
Pretty tough blow for a kid to weather.
But after what that psycho did to him... I think it could change things for the better.
No doubt of that.
He was that bad?
That bad, huh?
Must've been a relief then, when he left?
How'd he die?
Let's, uh, change the subject.
So, you're relieved now?
How did he die?
Let's change the subject.
I hope it's no more trouble for Randy.
His bike and the highway, that was his world. But at home... Lemme tell you a story.
This one time he took Dorian into the city. Had some errand to run, just father and son.
He came back that night, dead-ass drunk, ragin' at me for callin' the cops on him.
For weeks I cried every night.
My husband was killed. The father of my children.
I--I'm sorry...
Randy changed, he locked up, not to mention the other two I still had to raise...
Life was rough with him and without him. Sometimes there is no solution.
The Aldecaldos told me he died an honorable death. Whatever the hell that means.
They showed me his body... Where his face used to be. Couldn't see the honor in that.
When I thought I might never see my Randy again...
But all's well that ends well. I got Randy back... and my brother too.
Stay strong.
Hang in there, Joss.
Did you?
River found him in some dive and brought Dorian home.
River told me about your parents.
Joss... River told me about your parents...
He must really trust you. He'd hardly tell a soul about them.
It must've been a nightmare to see them die like that... How'd you hold up?
The orphanage put some things in perspective, but mostly it was us havin' each other. For a while.
But my brother's obsession got the better of him. Like he needed to catch all the world's killers with his own two hands.
Not really all bad. A cop with a calling's one rare breed.
I guess. But I prefer how he is now â€“ finally come to terms with life and himself.
I'm sorry, Joss...
Joss, I'm sorry...
You left them... Left them both... After you promised...
Joss, I... I...
My brother and my boy are dead. DEAD! Because of you!
I better never see you again... Ever.
